facilitate the request of copies of the credit and debit memos from the bank to determine their validity and immediately effect adjustment in the books, if warranted and inform the bank of the noted bank error and deposit in transit for adjustment in their records; 

trace with the Treasury Office the paid vouchers and details of the deposits that remained unrecorded and obtain the related documents for recording in the books; 

 identify the persons responsible for the incurrence of bank charges and demand the refund of the same otherwise recognize the liability; and 

effect adjustment on the identified stale checks and other valid reconciling items.

